## **ü¶Ü Task 5 \- The Mystery of the Repeated Digits**

One day, the ducks discovered a mysterious number carved into a rock by the pond.   
They noticed that some digits appear more than once, perhaps it‚Äôs a secret code\! They decided to read the number from end to start and call out each digit that appears multiple times. 

Ask the user to enter a positive number, then print all digits that appear more than once, starting from the last to the first. If a digit appears X times, print it (X-1) times. 

If there are no duplicates in the numbers, do not print anything.

If the input from the user is not valid, print the error message:  
![][image11]

The Mystery of the Repeated Digits 6. Good Night Ducks 5 please enter number 1234 Welcome to our games, please choose an option: 1. Ducky's Unity Game 2. The Memory Game 3. | :---- |

**Pay attention,** The duck begins to read the number from right to left. Each time it looks at a digit, it checks whether that number will appear again later as it continues reading. If the number doesn‚Äôt appear again, the duck simply waddles on to the next one. 

But if it will appear later \- the duck quacks the number loudly before moving on. So when the duck first sees the last 2, it notices there‚Äôs another 2 ahead and quacks, ‚Äú2 appears more than once\!‚Äù.   
Then, as it keeps reading, the same happens with the 3 \- it spots another one waiting further along the rock and quacks again. The duck continues this way until it reaches the start, always looking ahead for repeats and calling them out when it finds them \- a true detective of the pond‚Äôs secret code.
